LAGOS – The Governorship Candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party in Lagos State, Dr. Abdul-Azeez Olajide Adediran popularly called Jandor has expressed concern over the woes of families displaced by flood. Jandor in a press statement on Saturday stated that he has reached out to some of the victims earlier in the week, stressed that the situation became worrisome today with the torrential rain that has lasted for about seven hours. The statement reads, “I have received with worries, messages of families being displaced as a result of today’s downpour. It is disheartening to see the good people of the state suffer such neglect and huge discomfort. This disaster is preventable and avoidable at least to the barest minimum.” According to the statement, the governorship candidate has put up actions to mitigate the effect of the flood across the 20 Local Government areas of the state. “In the interim, I have set up a Disaster Recovery Team across the state from our network of members to offer immediate assistance to the victims” he said. The governorship candidate commiserated with the victims and prayed that there would be no loss of lives even as the rain still continues in some part of the state. “We will continue to patch up until we install a government we can jointly call our own and birth a breath of fresh air in Lagos,” he said. Victims are requested to call the underlisted numbersand persons for provision of support where necessary across the 20 local government areas of the state. . POLL Agege, Rasheed Osanyinpeju  on 08033041430, Ajeromi Ifelodun, Bodunde Ogunlana 08033357158 and Ovie 0802 307 6540 Others are, Alimosho, Almaroof Olalekan on 08055243705, Saminu Yahaya on 08052323621, Amuwo Odofin, Yahaya Hassan on 08034546909 and Adeniyi Owolabi 08034678234 The team for Apapa I’d Olanrewaju Dawood on 08024323838, Badagry,  Adeshina Dada on 08121584815, etcetera.